这是2019年发生在[[美国的大规模枪击事件|美国的大规模枪击事件]]的一份统计名单。大规模枪击事件是涉及到多名与枪支有关的暴力受害者的事件。然而其准确的纳入标准仍然存在争议，一直没有一个被广泛接受的定义。<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=Public Mass Shootings in the United States|url=https://fas.org/sgp/crs/misc/R43004.pdf|accessdate=2018-08-26|author=Bjelopera|date=2013-03-18|first=Jerome|work=Congressional Research Service|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130909213006/http://www.fas.org/sgp/crs/misc/R43004.pdf|archivedate=2013-09-09|dead-url=yes|quote="There is no broadly agreed-to, specific conceptualization of this issue, so this report uses its own definition for public mass shootings."}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=The squishy definition of 'mass shooting' complicates media coverage|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2017/10/04/the-squishy-definition-of-mass-shooting-complicates-media-coverage/|accessdate=2018-08-26|author=Borchers|date=2017-10-04|first=Callum|work=Washington Post|language=en|quote=...'mass shooting' is a term without a universally-accepted definition.|archive-date=2020-10-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201021213359/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2017/10/04/the-squishy-definition-of-mass-shooting-complicates-media-coverage/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

{{Internal link helper/en|枪支暴力档案室|Gun Violence Archive}}（GVA)，是一家追踪美国枪击案及其特征的非营利性研究组织，他们将大规模枪击事件的标准定义为：在一次枪击事件中，四人及以上（不包括犯罪者）大致在同一时间在一个地方被枪杀（或因此受伤）。<ref name=":5">{{Cite web|title=General Methodology|url=http://www.gunviolencearchive.org/methodology|accessdate=2018-08-27|author=|date=|first=|work=Gun Violence Archive}}</ref> 而[[國會研究處|国会研究处]]进一步缩小了该定义的范围，将其定义为“公共大规模射杀”事件，该定义只考虑受害者中被杀害的人，而不包括在事件中生还的受害者。<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=Public Mass Shootings in the United States|url=https://fas.org/sgp/crs/misc/R43004.pdf|accessdate=2018-08-26|author=Bjelopera|date=2013-03-18|first=Jerome|work=Congressional Research Service|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130909213006/http://www.fas.org/sgp/crs/misc/R43004.pdf|archivedate=2013-09-09|dead-url=yes|quote="There is no broadly agreed-to, specific conceptualization of this issue, so this report uses its own definition for public mass shootings."}}</ref> 《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》 和《{{Internal link helper/en|琼斯母亲|Mother Jones (magazine)}}》使用了与之类似的定义。国会研究处承认它们的定义"是对这个问题采取的保守措施"，因为许多此类事件中的死亡人数正在逐渐减少。<ref name=":2">{{Cite web|title=More than 50 years of U.S. mass shootings: The victims, sites, killers and weapons|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/graphics/2018/national/mass-shootings-in-america/|accessdate=2018-08-27|author=Berkowitz|date=2018-09-14|first=Bonnie|work=Washington Post|language=en|archive-date=2021-12-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211201062340/https://www.washingtonpost.com/graphics/2018/national/mass-shootings-in-america/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":3">{{Cite news|url=https://www.motherjones.com/politics/2012/07/mass-shootings-map/|title=A Guide to Mass Shootings in America|author=Follman|first=Mark|date=2018-09-20|work=Mother Jones|accessdate=2018-08-26|author2=Aronsen|first2=Gavin|language=en-US|last3=Pan|first3=Deanna|archive-date=2019-05-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190528235745/https://www.motherjones.com/politics/2012/07/mass-shootings-map/|dead-url=no}}</ref> [[众包|众包]]的大规模枪击跟踪项目将大规模枪击事件定义为"在一次单一的枪击事件中有四人或及以上被射中。这其中可能包括枪手本人，或被警察射中的枪手周围的平民。"<ref name=":4">{{Cite web|title=Mass Shooting Tracker|url=https://www.massshootingtracker.org/about|accessdate=2018-08-26|author=|date=|first=|work=Mass Shooting Tracker|archive-date=2018-01-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180104222719/https://www.massshootingtracker.org/about|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

截止到2019年7月31日，已有248次大规模枪击事件符合本条目的入选标准。平均每天发生1.2次此类枪击事件。在这些枪击案中，有979人受伤，246人死亡（共有1225名受害者）。

== 定义 ==
大规模枪击事件有很多种定义，以下列举出一些比较广泛使用的定义：

* [[史丹佛大學|斯坦福大学的]]MSA数据项目：在同一个地点，在大致相同的时间内，不包含犯罪者，遭到三次及以上射击的事件。（不包括有组织犯罪、以及帮派相关的和与药物有关的枪击事件）<ref>{{Cite web|title=Mass Shootings in America|url=https://library.stanford.edu/projects/mass-shootings-america|accessdate=2019-07-02|author=|date=|first=|work=Stanford Libraries|language=en|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20220107002501/https://library.stanford.edu/projects/mass-shootings-america|archivedate=2022-01-07|dead-url=no}}</ref>
* 大规模枪击事件追踪者：一次事件中，在一个地点，在大约同一时间内射击四次或更多次。<ref name=":4">{{Cite web|title=Mass Shooting Tracker|url=https://www.massshootingtracker.org/about|accessdate=2018-08-26|author=|date=|first=|work=Mass Shooting Tracker}}</ref>
* {{Internal link helper/en|枪支暴力档案室|Gun Violence Archive}}/''[[声音传媒|聲音傳媒]]''：在同一时间，在同一地点，不包括犯罪者，发生四起或更多事件。<ref name=":5">{{Cite web|title=General Methodology|url=http://www.gunviolencearchive.org/methodology|accessdate=2018-08-27|author=|date=|first=|work=Gun Violence Archive}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|author=Lopez|first=German|title=The debate over how to define mass shootings is ridiculous|url=https://www.vox.com/policy-and-politics/2015/12/4/9850758/mass-shooting-definition|date=2015-12-04|work=[[Vox_(magazine)|Vox]]|accessdate=2018-08-27|dead-url=no|archive-date=2022-01-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220104193158/https://www.vox.com/policy-and-politics/2015/12/4/9850758/mass-shooting-definition}}</ref>
* 《琼斯母亲》：一次事件中，在公共场所，不包括犯罪者，三人及以上被开枪杀害。<ref name=":3">{{Cite news|url=https://www.motherjones.com/politics/2012/07/mass-shootings-map/|title=A Guide to Mass Shootings in America|author=Follman|first=Mark|date=2018-09-20|work=Mother Jones|accessdate=2018-08-26|author2=Aronsen|first2=Gavin|language=en-US|last3=Pan|first3=Deanna}}</ref>
* 《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》：一次事件中，在公共场所，不包括犯罪者，四人及以上被开枪杀害。<ref name=":2">{{Cite web|title=More than 50 years of U.S. mass shootings: The victims, sites, killers and weapons|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/graphics/2018/national/mass-shootings-in-america/|accessdate=2018-08-27|author=Berkowitz|date=2018-09-14|first=Bonnie|work=Washington Post|language=en}}</ref>
* [[ABC新聞|ABC新闻]]/[[联邦调查局|联邦调查局]]：一次事件中，在同一地点，在大约同一时间，不包括犯罪者，四人及以上被开枪杀害。<ref name="ABC">{{Cite news|author=Keneally|first=Meghan|title=There were 2 deadly mass shootings a month so far in 2019|url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/deadly-mass-shootings-month-2019/story?id=63449799|date=2019-06-05|accessdate=2019-06-29|archive-date=2022-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220106022644/https://abcnews.go.com/US/deadly-mass-shootings-month-2019/story?id=63449799|dead-url=no}}</ref>
* [[國會研究處|美国国会研究服务]]：一次事件中，在公共场所，不包括犯罪者，不包括与帮派有关的杀人事件以及以利润为动机的事件，四人及以上被开枪杀害。<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=Public Mass Shootings in the United States|url=https://fas.org/sgp/crs/misc/R43004.pdf|accessdate=2018-08-26|author=Bjelopera|date=2013-03-18|first=Jerome|work=Congressional Research Service|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130909213006/http://www.fas.org/sgp/crs/misc/R43004.pdf|archivedate=2013-09-09|dead-url=yes|quote="There is no broadly agreed-to, specific conceptualization of this issue, so this report uses its own definition for public mass shootings."}}</ref>

